## Command
Aways use the `ng generate` command for any file generation. Examples:
- `ng generate component` or `ng g c`
- `ng generate service` or `ng g s`
- `ng generate module` or `ng g m`
- `ng generate directive` or `ng g d`
- `ng generate pipe` or `ng g p`
- `ng generate guard`
- `ng generate class`
- `ng generate interface`
- `ng generate enum`

## Modifications
- `ng generate component` - skip creating test (.spec.ts) files (--skip-tests)

## Guidelines
- ALWAYS create standalone components (--standalone=true), regardless of the existing code
- Don't create modules
- Use the newest angular practices
